<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9046] Connect worker configs require undocumented &apos;admin.&apos; prefix to configure DLQ for connectors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9046</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The changes for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8265&quot; title=&quot;Connect Client Config Override policy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8265&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8265&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;involved &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/6624/files#diff-316d2c222b623ee65e8065863bf4b9ceR606&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;adding a prefix of &quot;admin.&quot; to Connect worker configs&lt;/a&gt;&#160;that would be used to configure the admin client that&apos;s used for connector DLQs. However, this was never documented in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-458%3A+Connector+Client+Config+Override+Policy&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;corresponding KIP&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and has broken backwards compatibility with prior Connect releases since workers without the necessary &lt;tt&gt;&quot;admin.&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;-prefixed properties in their configuration files will now fail in some circumstances (e.g., when interacting with a secured Kafka cluster that requires authentication from all admin clients that interact with it).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13262460">KAFKA-9046</key>
            <summary>Connect worker configs require undocumented &apos;admin.&apos; prefix to configure DLQ for connectors</summary>
